  "riddle": "1. Seek the date when the second season of a popular entrepreneurial series aimed at Australian audiences made its debut. \n\n2. What bustling city serves as the operational heart for a major South African satellite television provider, bringing diverse content to households?\n\n3. How high do the grounds of this urban center rise above sea level—where dreams of broadcast innovation take root?\n\n4. Within this thriving community, how many hospitals exist to cater to its residents' health needs? Count them as you envision the support network surrounding entrepreneurs. \n\n5. Take a journey of numbers: Calculate the absolute difference between the elevation you discovered and the hospitals counted in the previous clue. \n\n6. Once more, revisit the altitude of this notable place—that number will soon lead you to your next answer. \n\n7. As you reflect on the name of the satellite provider you uncovered, how many vowels dance within its letters? Count them to continue the trail.\n\n8. Onward to the tale of a television operator, find the year when a certain service known for adapting programming to different timezones was declared obsolete. \n\n9. Combine the elevation you noted earlier in clue 6 with the year from clue 8: what remains when you add them together and find that sum modulo 10? \n\nThe final answer you seek will provide you with a single digit—from the calculations represented by clues 6 and 8.",
